<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN302-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai, atu; tuṟai, kutiraimaṟam. veṟipāṭiya kāmakkaṇṇiyār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN302">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>veṭivēy koḷvatu pōla vōṭit</l>
<l>tāvu pukaḷu māvē pūvē</l>
<l>viḷaṅkiḻai makaḷir kūntaṟ koṇṭa</l>
<l>narantap palkāḻk kōtai cuṟṟiya</l>
<l>vaitamai pāṇi vaṇarkōṭṭuc cīṟiyāḻk</l>
<l>kaivār narampiṉ pāṇark kōkkiya</l>
<l>nirampā viyalpiṟ karampaic cīṟūr</l>
<l>nōkkiṉarc cekukkuṅ kāḷai yūkki</l>
<l>vēli ṉaṭṭa kaḷiṟupeyart teṇṇiṉ</l>
<l>viṇṇivar vicumpiṉ mīṉun</l>
<l>taṇpeya luṟaiyu muṟaiyāṟ ṟāvē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Running, leaping as of receiving the cracking bamboo [rod],</l>
<l>prance the horses. The flowers, (1f.)</l>
<l corresp="3">the are taken for the tresses of girls with shining jewels. </l>
<l corresp="7">Little villages in the waste-land of an insufficient quality </l>
<l corresp="6">are offered to bards with strings strummed by hand </l>
<l corresp="5">on little lutes with curved necks [and] a wonderfully suited beat </l>
<l corresp="4">that wore many-strand garlands of bitter orange. </l>
<l corresp="8a-c">The young man who will destroy those who look at [them], </l>
<l corresp="8d-9">if you count again the elephants he killed with [his] spear, swinging [it], </l>
<l>they cannot match [in number] the stars in the sky</l>
<l>wandering across the firmament and the drops of cool rain. (10f.)</l>
</lg>
    </div>
